42勘 19:15 "And it came about that when he returned, after receiving the kingdom, he ordered that these slaves, to whom he had given the money, be called to him in order that he might know what business they had done.
42勘 19:16 "And the first appeared, saying, 'Master, your mina has made ten minas more.'
42勘 19:17 "And he said to him, 'Well done, good slave, because you have been faithful in a very little thing, be in authority over ten cities.'
42勘 19:18 "And the second came, saying, 'Your mina, master, has made five minas.'
42勘 19:19 "And he said to him also, 'And you are to be over five cities.'
42勘 19:20 "And another came, saying, 'Master, behold your mina, which I kept put away in a handkerchief;
42勘 19:21 for I was afraid of you, because you are an exacting man; you take up what you did not lay down, and reap what you did not sow. '
42勘 19:22 "He *said to him, 'By your own words I will judge you, you worthless slave. Did you know that I am an exacting man, taking up what I did not lay down, and reaping what I did not sow?
42勘 19:23 'Then why did you not put the money in the bank, and having come, I would have collected it with interest?'
42勘 19:24 "And he said to the bystanders, 'Take the mina away from him, and give it to the one who has the ten minas.'
42勘 19:25 "And they said to him, 'Master, he has ten minas [already.]'
42勘 19:26 "I tell you, that to everyone who has shall [more] be given, but from the one who does not have, even what he does have shall be taken away.
42勘 19:27 "But these enemies of mine, who did not want me to reign over them, bring them here and slay them in my presence."
42勘 19:28 And after He had said these things, He was going on ahead, ascending to Jerusalem.
42勘 19:29 And it came about that when He approached Bethphage and Bethany, near the mount that is called Olivet, He sent two of the disciples,
42勘 19:30 saying, "Go into the village opposite [you,] in which as you enter you will find a colt tied, on which no one yet has ever sat; untie it, and bring it [here.]
42勘 19:31 "And if anyone asks you, 'Why are you untying it?' thus shall you speak, 'The Lord has need of it.'"
42勘 19:32 And those who were sent went away and found it just as He had told them.
42勘 19:33 And as they were untying the colt, its owners said to them, "Why are you untying the colt?"
42勘 19:34 And they said, "The Lord has need of it."
42勘 19:35 And they brought it to Jesus, and they threw their garments on the colt, and put Jesus [on it.]
42勘 19:36 And as He was going, they were spreading their garments in the road.
42勘 19:37 And as He was now approaching, near the descent of the Mount of Olives, the whole multitude of the disciples began to praise God joyfully with a loud voice for all the miracles which they had seen,
42勘 19:38 saying, "BLESSED IS THE KING WHO COMES IN THE NAME OF THE LORD; Peace in heaven and glory in the highest!"
42勘 19:39 And some of the Pharisees in the multitude said to Him, "Teacher, rebuke Your disciples."
42勘 19:40 And He answered and said, "I tell you, if these become silent, the stones will cry out!"
42勘 19:41 And when He approached, He saw the city and wept over it,
42勘 19:42 saying, "If you had known in this day, even you, the things which make for peace! But now they have been hidden from your eyes.
42勘 19:43 "For the days shall come upon you when your enemies will throw up a bank before you, and surround you, and hem you in on every side,
42勘 19:44 and will level you to the ground and your children within you, and they will not leave in you one stone upon another, because you did not recognize the time of your visitation. "
42勘 19:45 And He entered the temple and began to cast out those who were selling,
42勘 19:46 saying to them, "It is written, 'AND MY HOUSE SHALL BE A HOUSE OF PRAYER,' but you have made it a Robbers' DEN."
42勘 19:47 And He was teaching daily in the temple; but the chief priests and the scribes and the leading men among the people were trying to destroy Him,
42勘 19:48 and they could not find anything that they might do, for all the people were hanging upon His words.
42勘 20:1 And it came about on one of the days while He was teaching the people in the temple and preaching the gospel, that the chief priests and the scribes with the elders confronted [Him,]
42勘 20:2 and they spoke, saying to Him, "Tell us by what authority You are doing these things, or who is the one who gave You this authority?"
42勘 20:3 And He answered and said to them, "I shall also ask you a question, and you tell Me
42勘 20:4 "Was the baptism of John from heaven or from men?"
42勘 20:5 And they reasoned among themselves, saying, "If we say, 'From heaven,' He will say, 'Why did you not believe him?'
42勘 20:6 "But if we say, 'From men,' all the people will stone us to death, for they are convinced that John was a prophet."
42勘 20:7 And they answered that they did not know where [it came] from.
42勘 20:8 And Jesus said to them, "Neither will I tell you by what authority I do these things."
42勘 20:9 And He began to tell the people this parable "A man planted a vineyard and rented it out to vine-growers, and went on a journey for a long time.
42勘 20:10 "And at the [harvest] time he sent a slave to the vine-growers, in order that they might give him [some] of the produce of the vineyard; but the vine-growers beat him and sent him away empty-handed.
42勘 20:11 "And he proceeded to send another slave; and they beat him also and treated him shamefully, and sent him away empty-handed.
42勘 20:12 "And he proceeded to send a third; and this one also they wounded and cast out.
42勘 20:13 "And the owner of the vineyard said, 'What shall I do? I will send my beloved son; perhaps they will respect him.'
42勘 20:14 "But when the vine-growers saw him, they reasoned with one another, saying, 'This is the heir; let us kill him that the inheritance may be ours.'
42勘 20:15 "And they threw him out of the vineyard and killed him. What, therefore, will the owner of the vineyard do to them?
42勘 20:16 "He will come and destroy these vine-growers and will give the vineyard to others." And when they heard it, they said, "May it never be!"
42勘 20:17 But He looked at them and said, "What then is this that is written, 'THE STONE WHICH THE BUILDERS REJECTED, THIS BECAME THE CHIEF CORNER [stone]'?
42勘 20:18 "Everyone who falls on that stone will be broken to pieces; but on whomever it falls, it will scatter him like dust."
42勘 20:19 And the scribes and the chief priests tried to lay hands on Him that very hour, and they feared the people; for they understood that He spoke this parable against them.
42勘 20:20 And they watched Him, and sent spies who pretended to be righteous, in order that they might catch Him in some statement, so as to deliver Him up to the rule and the authority of the governor.
42勘 20:21 And they questioned Him, saying, "Teacher, we know that You speak and teach correctly, and You are not partial to any, but teach the way of God in truth.
42勘 20:22 "Is it lawful for us to pay taxes to Caesar, or not?"
42勘 20:23 But He detected their trickery and said to them,
42勘 20:24 "Show Me a denarius. Whose likeness and inscription does it have?" And they said," Caesar's. "
42勘 20:25 And He said to them, "Then render to Caesar the things that are Caesar's, and to God the things that are God's."
42勘 20:26 And they were unable to catch Him in a saying in the presence of the people; and marveling at His answer, they became silent.
42勘 20:27 Now there came to Him some of the Sadducees (who say that there is no resurrection),
42勘 20:28 and they questioned Him, saying, "Teacher, Moses wrote for us that IF A Man's BROTHER DIES, having a wife, AND HE IS CHILDLESS, HIS BROTHER SHOULD TAKE THE WIFE AND RAISE UP OFFSPRING TO HIS BROTHER.
42勘 20:29 "Now there were seven brothers; and the first took a wife, and died childless;
42勘 20:30 and the second
42勘 20:31 and the third took her; and in the same way all seven died, leaving no children.
42勘 20:32 "Finally the woman died also.
42勘 20:33 "In the resurrection therefore, which one's wife will she be? For all seven had her as wife."
42勘 20:34 And Jesus said to them, "The sons of this age marry and are given in marriage,
42勘 20:35 but those who are considered worthy to attain to that age and the resurrection from the dead, neither marry, nor are given in marriage;
42勘 20:36 for neither can they die anymore, for they are like angels, and are sons of God, being sons of the resurrection.
42勘 20:37 "But that the dead are raised, even Moses showed, in the [passage about the burning] bush, where he calls the Lord THE GOD OF ABRAHAM, AND THE GOD OF ISAAC, AND THE GOD OF JACOB.
42勘 20:38 "Now He is not the God of the dead, but of the living; for all live to Him."
42勘 20:39 And some of the scribes answered and said, "Teacher, You have spoken well."
42勘 20:40 For they did not have courage to question Him any longer about anything.
42勘 20:41 And He said to them, "How [is it that] they say the Christ is David's son?
42勘 20:42 "For David himself says in the book of Psalms, 'THE LORD SAID TO MY LORD," SIT AT MY RIGHT HAND,
42勘 20:43 UNTIL I MAKE THINE ENEMIES A FOOTSTOOL FOR THY FEET. "'
42勘 20:44 "David therefore calls Him 'Lord,' and how is He his son?"
42勘 20:45 And while all the people were listening, He said to the disciples,
42勘 20:46 "Beware of the scribes, who like to walk around in long robes, and love respectful greetings in the market places, and chief seats in the synagogues, and places of honor at banquets,
42勘 20:47 who devour widows' houses, and for appearance's sake offer long prayers; these will receive greater condemnation. "
42勘 21:1 And He looked up and saw the rich putting their gifts into the treasury.
42勘 21:2 And He saw a certain poor widow putting in two small copper coins.
42勘 21:3 And He said, "Truly I say to you, this poor widow put in more than all [of them;]
42勘 21:4 for they all out of their surplus put into the offering; but she out of her poverty put in all that she had to live on. "
42勘 21:5 And while some were talking about the temple, that it was adorned with beautiful stones and votive gifts, He said,
42勘 21:6 "[As for] these things which you are looking at, the days will come in which there will not be left one stone upon another which will not be torn down."
42勘 21:7 And they questioned Him, saying, "Teacher, when therefore will these things be? And what [will be] the sign when these things are about to take place?"
42勘 21:8 And He said, "See to it that you be not misled; for many will come in My name, saying, 'I am [He,'] and, 'The time is at hand'; do not go after them.
42勘 21:9 "And when you hear of wars and disturbances, do not be terrified; for these things must take place first, but the end [does] not [follow] immediately."
42勘 21:10 Then He continued by saying to them, "Nation will rise against nation, and kingdom against kingdom,
42勘 21:11 and there will be great earthquakes, and in various places plagues and famines; and there will be terrors and great signs from heaven.
42勘 21:12 "But before all these things, they will lay their hands on you and will persecute you, delivering you to the synagogues and prisons, bringing you before kings and governors for My name's sake.
42勘 21:13 "It will lead to an opportunity for your testimony.
42勘 21:14 "So make up your minds not to prepare beforehand to defend yourselves;
42勘 21:15 for I will give you utterance and wisdom which none of your opponents will be able to resist or refute.
42勘 21:16 "But you will be delivered up even by parents and brothers and relatives and friends, and they will put [some] of you to death,
42勘 21:17 and you will be hated by all on account of My name.
42勘 21:18 "Yet not a hair of your head will perish.
42勘 21:19 "By your endurance you will gain your lives.
42勘 21:20 "But when you see Jerusalem surrounded by armies, then recognize that her desolation is at hand.
42勘 21:21 "Then let those who are in Judea flee to the mountains, and let those who are in the midst of the city depart, and let not those who are in the country enter the city;
42勘 21:22 because these are days of vengeance, in order that all things which are written may be fulfilled.
42勘 21:23 "Woe to those who are with child and to those who nurse babes in those days; for there will be great distress upon the land, and wrath to this people,
42勘 21:24 and they will fall by the edge of the sword, and will be led captive into all the nations; and Jerusalem will be trampled under foot by the Gentiles until the times of the Gentiles be fulfilled.
42勘 21:25 "And there will be signs in sun and moon and stars, and upon the earth dismay among nations, in perplexity at the roaring of the sea and the waves,
42勘 21:26 men fainting from fear and the expectation of the things which are coming upon the world; for the powers of the heavens will be shaken.
42勘 21:27 "And then they will see THE SON OF MAN COMING IN A CLOUD with power and great glory.
42勘 21:28 "But when these things begin to take place, straighten up and lift up your heads, because your redemption is drawing near."
42勘 21:29 And He told them a parable "Behold the fig tree and all the trees;
42勘 21:30 as soon as they put forth [leaves,] you see it and know for yourselves that summer is now near.
42勘 21:31 "Even so you, too, when you see these things happening, recognize that the kingdom of God is near.
42勘 21:32 "Truly I say to you, this generation will not pass away until all things take place.
42勘 21:33 "Heaven and earth will pass away, but My words will not pass away.
42勘 21:34 "Be on guard, that your hearts may not be weighted down with dissipation and drunkenness and the worries of life, and that day come on you suddenly like a trap;
42勘 21:35 for it will come upon all those who dwell on the face of all the earth.
42勘 21:36 "But keep on the alert at all times, praying in order that you may have strength to escape all these things that are about to take place, and to stand before the Son of Man."
42勘 21:37 Now during the day He was teaching in the temple, but at evening He would go out and spend the night on the mount that is called Olivet.
42勘 21:38 And all the people would get up early in the morning [to come] to Him in the temple to listen to Him.
42勘 22:1 Now the Feast of Unleavened Bread, which is called the Passover, was approaching.
42勘 22:2 And the chief priests and the scribes were seeking how they might put Him to death; for they were afraid of the people.
42勘 22:3 And Satan entered into Judas who was called Iscariot, belonging to the number of the twelve.
42勘 22:4 And he went away and discussed with the chief priests and officers how he might betray Him to them.
42勘 22:5 And they were glad, and agreed to give him money.
42勘 22:6 And he consented, and [began] seeking a good opportunity to betray Him to them apart from the multitude.
42勘 22:7 Then came the [first] day of Unleavened Bread on which the Passover [lamb] had to be sacrificed.
42勘 22:8 And He sent Peter and John, saying, "Go and prepare the Passover for us, that we may eat it."
42勘 22:9 And they said to Him, "Where do You want us to prepare it?"
42勘 22:10 And He said to them, "Behold, when you have entered the city, a man will meet you carrying a pitcher of water; follow him into the house that he enters.
42勘 22:11 "And you shall say to the owner of the house, 'The Teacher says to you," Where is the guest room in which I may eat the Passover with My disciples? "'
42勘 22:12 "And he will show you a large, furnished, upper room; prepare it there."
42勘 22:13 And they departed and found [everything] just as He had told them; and they prepared the Passover.
42勘 22:14 And when the hour had come He reclined [at the table,] and the apostles with Him.
42勘 22:15 And He said to them, "I have earnestly desired to eat this Passover with you before I suffer;
42勘 22:16 for I say to you, I shall never again eat it until it is fulfilled in the kingdom of God. "
42勘 22:17 And when He had taken a cup [and] given thanks, He said, "Take this and share it among yourselves;
42勘 22:18 for I say to you, I will not drink of the fruit of the vine from now on until the kingdom of God comes. "
42勘 22:19 And when He had taken [some] bread [and] given thanks, He broke [it,] and gave [it] to them, saying, "This is My body which is given for you; do this in remembrance of Me."
42勘 22:20 And in the same way [He took] the cup after they had eaten, saying, "This cup which is poured out for you is the new covenant in My blood.
42勘 22:21 "But behold, the hand of the one betraying Me is with Me on the table.
42勘 22:22 "For indeed, the Son of Man is going as it has been determined; but woe to that man by whom He is betrayed!"
42勘 22:23 And they began to discuss among themselves which one of them it might be who was going to do this thing.
42勘 22:24 And there arose also a dispute among them [as to] which one of them was regarded to be greatest.
42勘 22:25 And He said to them, "The kings of the Gentiles lord it over them; and those who have authority over them are called 'Benefactors.'
42勘 22:26 "But not so with you, but let him who is the greatest among you become as the youngest, and the leader as the servant.
42勘 22:27 "For who is greater, the one who reclines [at the table,] or the one who serves? Is it not the one who reclines [at the table]? But I am among you as the one who serves.
42勘 22:28 "And you are those who have stood by Me in My trials;
42勘 22:29 and just as My Father has granted Me a kingdom, I grant you
42勘 22:30 that you may eat and drink at My table in My kingdom, and you will sit on thrones judging the twelve tribes of Israel.
42勘 22:31 "Simon, Simon, behold, Satan has demanded [permission] to sift you like wheat;
42勘 22:32 but I have prayed for you, that your faith may not fail; and you, when once you have turned again, strengthen your brothers. "
42勘 22:33 And he said to Him, "Lord, with You I am ready to go both to prison and to death!"
42勘 22:34 And He said, "I say to you, Peter, the cock will not crow today until you have denied three times that you know Me."
42勘 22:35 And He said to them, "When I sent you out without purse and bag and sandals, you did not lack anything, did you?" And they said, "[No,] nothing."
42勘 22:36 And He said to them, "But now, let him who has a purse take it along, likewise also a bag, and let him who has no sword sell his robe and buy one.
42勘 22:37 "For I tell you, that this which is written must be fulfilled in Me, 'AND HE WAS NUMBERED WITH TRANSGRESSORS'; for that which refers to Me has [its] fulfillment."
42勘 22:38 And they said, "Lord, look, here are two swords." And He said to them, "It is enough."
42勘 22:39 And He came out and proceeded as was His custom to the Mount of Olives; and the disciples also followed Him.
42勘 22:40 And when He arrived at the place, He said to them, "Pray that you may not enter into temptation."
42勘 22:41 And He withdrew from them about a stone's throw, and He knelt down and [began] to pray,
42勘 22:42 saying, "Father, if Thou art willing, remove this cup from Me; yet not My will, but Thine be done."
42勘 22:43 Now an angel from heaven appeared to Him, strengthening Him.
42勘 22:44 And being in agony He was praying very fervently; and His sweat became like drops of blood, falling down upon the ground.
42勘 22:45 And when He rose from prayer, He came to the disciples and found them sleeping from sorrow,
42勘 22:46 and said to them, "Why are you sleeping? Rise and pray that you may not enter into temptation."
42勘 22:47 While He was still speaking, behold, a multitude [came,] and the one called Judas, one of the twelve, was preceding them; and he approached Jesus to kiss Him.
42勘 22:48 But Jesus said to him, "Judas, are you betraying the Son of Man with a kiss?"
42勘 22:49 And when those who were around Him saw what was going to happen, they said, "Lord, shall we strike with the sword?"
42勘 22:50 And a certain one of them struck the slave of the high priest and cut off his right ear.
42勘 22:51 But Jesus answered and said, "Stop! No more of this." And He touched his ear and healed him.
42勘 22:52 And Jesus said to the chief priests and officers of the temple and elders who had come against Him, "Have you come out with swords and clubs as against a robber?
42勘 22:53 "While I was with you daily in the temple, you did not lay hands on Me; but this hour and the power of darkness are yours."
42勘 22:54 And having arrested Him, they led Him [away,] and brought Him to the house of the high priest; but Peter was following at a distance.
42勘 22:55 And after they had kindled a fire in the middle of the courtyard and had sat down together, Peter was sitting among them.
42勘 22:56 And a certain servant-girl, seeing him as he sat in the firelight, and looking intently at him, said, "This man was with Him too."
42勘 22:57 But he denied [it,] saying, "Woman, I do not know Him."
42勘 22:58 And a little later, another saw him and said, "You are [one] of them too!" But Peter said, "Man, I am not!"
42勘 22:59 And after about an hour had passed, another man [began] to insist, saying, "Certainly this man also was with Him, for he is a Galilean too."
42勘 22:60 But Peter said, "Man, I do not know what you are talking about." And immediately, while he was still speaking, a cock crowed.
42勘 22:61 And the Lord turned and looked at Peter. And Peter remembered the word of the Lord, how He had told him, "Before a cock crows today, you will deny Me three times."
42勘 22:62 And he went out and wept bitterly.
42勘 22:63 And the men who were holding Jesus in custody were mocking Him, and beating Him,
42勘 22:64 and they blindfolded Him and were asking Him, saying, "Prophesy, who is the one who hit You?"
42勘 22:65 And they were saying many other things against Him, blaspheming.
42勘 22:66 And when it was day, the Council of elders of the people assembled, both chief priests and scribes, and they led Him away to their council [chamber,] saying,
42勘 22:67 "If You are the Christ, tell us." But He said to them, "If I tell you, you will not believe;
42勘 22:68 and if I ask a question, you will not answer.
42勘 22:69 "But from now on THE SON OF MAN WILL BE SEATED AT THE RIGHT HAND of the power OF GOD. "
42勘 22:70 And they all said, "Are You the Son of God, then?" And He said to them, "Yes, I am."
42勘 22:71 And they said, "What further need do we have of testimony? For we have heard it ourselves from His own mouth."
42勘 23:1 Then the whole body of them arose and brought Him before Pilate.
42勘 23:2 And they began to accuse Him, saying, "We found this man misleading our nation and forbidding to pay taxes to Caesar, and saying that He Himself is Christ, a King."
42勘 23:3 And Pilate asked Him, saying, "Are You the King of the Jews?" And He answered him and said, "[It is as] you say."
42勘 23:4 And Pilate said to the chief priests and the multitudes, "I find no guilt in this man."
42勘 23:5 But they kept on insisting, saying, "He stirs up the people, teaching all over Judea, starting from Galilee, even as far as this place."
42勘 23:6 But when Pilate heard it, he asked whether the man was a Galilean.
42勘 23:7 And when he learned that He belonged to Herod's jurisdiction, he sent Him to Herod, who himself also was in Jerusalem at that time.
42勘 23:8 Now Herod was very glad when he saw Jesus; for he had wanted to see Him for a long time, because he had been hearing about Him and was hoping to see some sign performed by Him.
42勘 23:9 And he questioned Him at some length; but He answered him nothing.
42勘 23:10 And the chief priests and the scribes were standing there, accusing Him vehemently.
42勘 23:11 And Herod with his soldiers, after treating Him with contempt and mocking Him, dressed Him in a gorgeous robe and sent Him back to Pilate.
42勘 23:12 Now Herod and Pilate became friends with one another that very day; for before they had been at enmity with each other.
42勘 23:13 And Pilate summoned the chief priests and the rulers and the people,
42勘 23:14 and said to them, "You brought this man to me as one who incites the people to rebellion, and behold, having examined Him before you, I have found no guilt in this man regarding the charges which you make against Him.
42勘 23:15 "No, nor has Herod, for he sent Him back to us; and behold, nothing deserving death has been done by Him.
42勘 23:16 "I will therefore punish Him and release Him."
42勘 23:17 {Now he was obliged to release to them at the feast one prisoner.}
42勘 23:18 But they cried out all together, saying, "Away with this man, and release for us Barabbas!"
42勘 23:19 (He was one who had been thrown into prison for a certain insurrection made in the city, and for murder.)
42勘 23:20 And Pilate, wanting to release Jesus, addressed them again,
42勘 23:21 but they kept on calling out, saying, "Crucify, crucify Him!"
42勘 23:22 And he said to them the third time, "Why, what evil has this man done? I have found in Him no guilt [demanding] death; I will therefore punish Him and release Him."
42勘 23:23 But they were insistent, with loud voices asking that He be crucified. And their voices [began] to prevail.
42勘 23:24 And Pilate pronounced sentence that their demand should be granted.
42勘 23:25 And he released the man they were asking for who had been thrown into prison for insurrection and murder, but he delivered Jesus to their will.
42勘 23:26 And when they led Him away, they laid hold of one Simon of Cyrene, coming in from the country, and placed on him the cross to carry behind Jesus.
42勘 23:27 And there were following Him a great multitude of the people, and of women who were mourning and lamenting Him.
42勘 23:28 But Jesus turning to them said, "Daughters of Jerusalem, stop weeping for Me, but weep for yourselves and for your children.
42勘 23:29 "For behold, the days are coming when they will say, 'Blessed are the barren, and the wombs that never bore, and the breasts that never nursed.'
42勘 23:30 "Then they will begin TO SAY TO THE MOUNTAINS, 'FALL ON US,' AND TO THE HILLS, 'COVER US.'
42勘 23:31 "For if they do these things in the green tree, what will happen in the dry?"
42勘 23:32 And two others also, who were criminals, were being led away to be put to death with Him.
42勘 23:33 And when they came to the place called The Skull, there they crucified Him and the criminals, one on the right and the other on the left.
42勘 23:34 But Jesus was saying, "Father, forgive them; for they do not know what they are doing." And they cast lots, dividing up His garments among themselves.
42勘 23:35 And the people stood by, looking on. And even the rulers were sneering at Him, saying, "He saved others; let Him save Himself if this is the Christ of God, His Chosen One."
42勘 23:36 And the soldiers also mocked Him, coming up to Him, offering Him sour wine,
42勘 23:37 and saying, "If You are the King of the Jews, save Yourself!"
42勘 23:38 Now there was also an inscription above Him, "THIS IS THE KING OF THE JEWS."
42勘 23:39 And one of the criminals who were hanged [there] was hurling abuse at Him, saying, "Are You not the Christ? Save Yourself and us!"
42勘 23:40 But the other answered, and rebuking him said, "Do you not even fear God, since you are under the same sentence of condemnation?
42勘 23:41 "And we indeed justly, for we are receiving what we deserve for our deeds; but this man has done nothing wrong."
42勘 23:42 And he was saying, "Jesus, remember me when You come in Your kingdom!"
42勘 23:43 And He said to him, "Truly I say to you, today you shall be with Me in Paradise."
42勘 23:44 And it was now about the sixth hour, and darkness fell over the whole land until the ninth hour,
42勘 23:45 the sun being obscured; and the veil of the temple was torn in two.
42勘 23:46 And Jesus, crying out with a loud voice, said, "Father, INTO THY HANDS I COMMIT MY SPIRIT." And having said this, He breathed His last.
42勘 23:47 Now when the centurion saw what had happened, he [began] praising God, saying, "Certainly this man was innocent."
42勘 23:48 And all the multitudes who came together for this spectacle, when they observed what had happened, [began] to return, beating their breasts.
