42勘 24:24 "And some of those who were with us went to the tomb and found it just exactly as the women also had said; but Him they did not see."
42勘 24:25 And He said to them, "O foolish men and slow of heart to believe in all that the prophets have spoken!
42勘 24:26 "Was it not necessary for the Christ to suffer these things and to enter into His glory?"
42勘 24:27 And beginning with Moses and with all the prophets, He explained to them the things concerning Himself in all the Scriptures.
42勘 24:28 And they approached the village where they were going, and He acted as though He would go farther.
42勘 24:29 And they urged Him, saying, "Stay with us, for it is [getting] toward evening, and the day is now nearly over." And He went in to stay with them.
42勘 24:30 And it came about that when He had reclined [at the table] with them, He took the bread and blessed [it,] and breaking [it,] He [began] giving [it] to them.
42勘 24:31 And their eyes were opened and they recognized Him; and He vanished from their sight.
42勘 24:32 And they said to one another, "Were not our hearts burning within us while He was speaking to us on the road, while He was explaining the Scriptures to us?"
42勘 24:33 And they arose that very hour and returned to Jerusalem, and found gathered together the eleven and those who were with them,
42勘 24:34 saying, "The Lord has really risen, and has appeared to Simon."
42勘 24:35 And they [began] to relate their experiences on the road and how He was recognized by them in the breaking of the bread.
42勘 24:36 And while they were telling these things, He Himself stood in their midst.
42勘 24:37 But they were startled and frightened and thought that they were seeing a spirit.
42勘 24:38 And He said to them, "Why are you troubled, and why do doubts arise in your hearts?
42勘 24:39 "See My hands and My feet, that it is I Myself; touch Me and see, for a spirit does not have flesh and bones as you see that I have."
42勘 24:40 {And when He had said this, He showed them His hands and His feet.}
42勘 24:41 And while they still could not believe [it] for joy and were marveling, He said to them, "Have you anything here to eat?"
42勘 24:42 And they gave Him a piece of a broiled fish;
