42勘 24:44 Now He said to them, "These are My words which I spoke to you while I was still with you, that all things which are written about Me in the Law of Moses and the Prophets and the Psalms must be fulfilled."
42勘 24:45 Then He opened their minds to understand the Scriptures,
42勘 24:46 and He said to them, "Thus it is written, that the Christ should suffer and rise again from the dead the third day;
42勘 24:47 and that repentance for forgiveness of sins should be proclaimed in His name to all the nations, beginning from Jerusalem.
42勘 24:48 "You are witnesses of these things.
42勘 24:49 "And behold, I am sending forth the promise of My Father upon you; but you are to stay in the city until you are clothed with power from on high."
42勘 24:50 And He led them out as far as Bethany, and He lifted up His hands and blessed them.
42勘 24:51 And it came about that while He was blessing them, He parted from them.
42勘 24:52 And they returned to Jerusalem with great joy,
42勘 24:53 and were continually in the temple, praising God.
