43推 5:9 And immediately the man became well, and took up his pallet and [began] to walk. Now it was the Sabbath on that day.
43推 5:10 Therefore the Jews were saying to him who was cured, "It is the Sabbath, and it is not permissible for you to carry your pallet."
43推 5:11 But he answered them, "He who made me well was the one who said to me, 'Take up your pallet and walk.'"
43推 5:12 They asked him, "Who is the man who said to you, 'Take up [your pallet,] and walk'?"
43推 5:13 But he who was healed did not know who it was; for Jesus had slipped away while there was a crowd in [that] place.
43推 5:14 Afterward Jesus *found him in the temple, and said to him, "Behold, you have become well; do not sin anymore, so that nothing worse may befall you."
43推 5:15 The man went away, and told the Jews that it was Jesus who had made him well.
43推 5:16 And for this reason the Jews were persecuting Jesus, because He was doing these things on the Sabbath.
43推 5:17 But He answered them, "My Father is working until now, and I Myself am working."
43推 5:18 For this cause therefore the Jews were seeking all the more to kill Him, because He not only was breaking the Sabbath, but also was calling God His own Father, making Himself equal with God.
43推 5:19 Jesus therefore answered and was saying to them, "Truly, truly, I say to you, the Son can do nothing of Himself, unless [it is] something He sees the Father doing; for whatever [the Father] does, these things the Son also does in like manner.
43推 5:20 "For the Father loves the Son, and shows Him all things that He Himself is doing; and greater works than these will He show Him, that you may marvel.
43推 5:21 "For just as the Father raises the dead and gives them life, even so the Son also gives life to whom He wishes.
43推 5:22 "For not even the Father judges anyone, but He has given all judgment to the Son,
43推 5:23 in order that all may honor the Son, even as they honor the Father. He who does not honor the Son does not honor the Father who sent Him.
43推 5:24 "Truly, truly, I say to you, he who hears My word, and believes Him who sent Me, has eternal life, and does not come into judgment, but has passed out of death into life.
43推 5:25 "Truly, truly, I say to you, an hour is coming and now is, when the dead shall hear the voice of the Son of God; and those who hear shall live.
43推 5:26 "For just as the Father has life in Himself, even so He gave to the Son also to have life in Himself;
43推 5:27 and He gave Him authority to execute judgment, because He is [the] Son of Man.
43推 5:28 "Do not marvel at this; for an hour is coming, in which all who are in the tombs shall hear His voice,
43推 5:29 and shall come forth; those who did the good [deeds] to a resurrection of life, those who committed the evil [deeds] to a resurrection of judgment.
43推 5:30 "I can do nothing on My own initiative. As I hear, I judge; and My judgment is just, because I do not seek My own will, but the will of Him who sent Me.
43推 5:31 "If I [alone] bear witness of Myself, My testimony is not true.
43推 5:32 "There is another who bears witness of Me, and I know that the testimony which He bears of Me is true.
43推 5:33 "You have sent to John, and he has borne witness to the truth.
43推 5:34 "But the witness which I receive is not from man, but I say these things that you may be saved.
43推 5:35 "He was the lamp that was burning and was shining and you were willing to rejoice for a while in his light.
43推 5:36 "But the witness which I have is greater than [that of] John; for the works which the Father has given Me to accomplish, the very works that I do, bear witness of Me, that the Father has sent Me.
43推 5:37 "And the Father who sent Me, He has borne witness of Me. You have neither heard His voice at any time, nor seen His form.
43推 5:38 "And you do not have His word abiding in you, for you do not believe Him whom He sent.
43推 5:39 "You search the Scriptures, because you think that in them you have eternal life; and it is these that bear witness of Me;
43推 5:40 and you are unwilling to come to Me, that you may have life.
43推 5:41 "I do not receive glory from men;
43推 5:42 but I know you, that you do not have the love of God in yourselves.
43推 5:43 "I have come in My Father's name, and you do not receive Me; if another shall come in his own name, you will receive him.
43推 5:44 "How can you believe, when you receive glory from one another, and you do not seek the glory that is from the [one and] only God?
43推 5:45 "Do not think that I will accuse you before the Father; the one who accuses you is Moses, in whom you have set your hope.
43推 5:46 "For if you believed Moses, you would believe Me; for he wrote of Me.
43推 5:47 "But if you do not believe his writings, how will you believe My words?"
43推 6:1 After these things Jesus went away to the other side of the Sea of Galilee (or Tiberias).
43推 6:2 And a great multitude was following Him, because they were seeing the signs which He was performing on those who were sick.
43推 6:3 And Jesus went up on the mountain, and there He sat with His disciples.
43推 6:4 Now the Passover, the feast of the Jews, was at hand.
43推 6:5 Jesus therefore lifting up His eyes, and seeing that a great multitude was coming to Him, *said to Philip, "Where are we to buy bread, that these may eat?"
43推 6:6 And this He was saying to test him; for He Himself knew what He was intending to do.
43推 6:7 Philip answered Him, "Two hundred denarii worth of bread is not sufficient for them, for everyone to receive a little."
43推 6:8 One of His disciples, Andrew, Simon Peter's brother, *said to Him,
43推 6:9 "There is a lad here who has five barley loaves and two fish, but what are these for so many people?"
43推 6:10 Jesus said, "Have the people sit down." Now there was much grass in the place. So the men sat down, in number about five thousand.
43推 6:11 Jesus therefore took the loaves; and having given thanks, He distributed to those who were seated; likewise also of the fish as much as they wanted.
43推 6:12 And when they were filled, He *said to His disciples, "Gather up the leftover fragments that nothing may be lost."
43推 6:13 And so they gathered them up, and filled twelve baskets with fragments from the five barley loaves, which were left over by those who had eaten.
43推 6:14 When therefore the people saw the sign which He had performed, they said, "This is of a truth the Prophet who is to come into the world."
43推 6:15 Jesus therefore perceiving that they were intending to come and take Him by force, to make Him king, withdrew again to the mountain by Himself alone.
43推 6:16 Now when evening came, His disciples went down to the sea,
43推 6:17 and after getting into a boat, they [started to] cross the sea to Capernaum. And it had already become dark, and Jesus had not yet come to them.
43推 6:18 And the sea [began] to be stirred up because a strong wind was blowing.
43推 6:19 When therefore they had rowed about three or four miles, they *beheld Jesus walking on the sea and drawing near to the boat; and they were frightened.
43推 6:20 But He *said to them, "It is I; do not be afraid."
43推 6:21 They were willing therefore to receive Him into the boat; and immediately the boat was at the land to which they were going.
43推 6:22 The next day the multitude that stood on the other side of the sea saw that there was no other small boat there, except one, and that Jesus had not entered with His disciples into the boat, but [that] His disciples had gone away alone.
43推 6:23 There came other small boats from Tiberias near to the place where they ate the bread after the Lord had given thanks.
43推 6:24 When the multitude therefore saw that Jesus was not there, nor His disciples, they themselves got into the small boats, and came to Capernaum, seeking Jesus.
43推 6:25 And when they found Him on the other side of the sea, they said to Him, "Rabbi, when did You get here?"
43推 6:26 Jesus answered them and said, "Truly, truly, I say to you, you seek Me, not because you saw signs, but because you ate of the loaves, and were filled.
43推 6:27 "Do not work for the food which perishes, but for the food which endures to eternal life, which the Son of Man shall give to you, for on Him the Father, [even] God, has set His seal."
43推 6:28 They said therefore to Him, "What shall we do, that we may work the works of God?"
43推 6:29 Jesus answered and said to them, "This is the work of God, that you believe in Him whom He has sent."
43推 6:30 They said therefore to Him, "What then do You do for a sign, that we may see, and believe You? What work do You perform?
43推 6:31 "Our fathers ate the manna in the wilderness; as it is written, ' HE GAVE THEM BREAD OUT OF HEAVEN TO EAT. '"
43推 6:32 Jesus therefore said to them, "Truly, truly, I say to you, it is not Moses who has given you the bread out of heaven, but it is My Father who gives you the true bread out of heaven.
43推 6:33 "For the bread of God is that which comes down out of heaven, and gives life to the world."
43推 6:34 They said therefore to Him, "Lord, evermore give us this bread."
43推 6:35 Jesus said to them, "I am the bread of life; he who comes to Me shall not hunger, and he who believes in Me shall never thirst.
43推 6:36 "But I said to you, that you have seen Me, and yet do not believe.
43推 6:37 "All that the Father gives Me shall come to Me, and the one who comes to Me I will certainly not cast out.
43推 6:38 "For I have come down from heaven, not to do My own will, but the will of Him who sent Me.
43推 6:39 "And this is the will of Him who sent Me, that of all that He has given Me I lose nothing, but raise it up on the last day.
43推 6:40 "For this is the will of My Father, that everyone who beholds the Son and believes in Him, may have eternal life; and I Myself will raise him up on the last day."
43推 6:41 The Jews therefore were grumbling about Him, because He said, "I am the bread that came down out of heaven."
43推 6:42 And they were saying, "Is not this Jesus, the son of Joseph, whose father and mother we know? How does He now say, 'I have come down out of heaven'?"
43推 6:43 Jesus answered and said to them, "Do not grumble among yourselves.
43推 6:44 "No one can come to Me, unless the Father who sent Me draws him; and I will raise him up on the last day.
43推 6:45 "It is written in the prophets, 'AND THEY SHALL ALL BE TAUGHT OF GOD.' Everyone who has heard and learned from the Father, comes to Me.
43推 6:46 "Not that any man has seen the Father, except the One who is from God; He has seen the Father.
43推 6:47 "Truly, truly, I say to you, he who believes has eternal life.
43推 6:48 "I am the bread of life.
43推 6:49 "Your fathers ate the manna in the wilderness, and they died.
43推 6:50 "This is the bread which comes down out of heaven, so that one may eat of it and not die.
43推 6:51 "I am the living bread that came down out of heaven; if anyone eats of this bread, he shall live forever; and the bread also which I shall give for the life of the world is My flesh."
43推 6:52 The Jews therefore [began] to argue with one another, saying, "How can this man give us [His] flesh to eat?"
43推 6:53 Jesus therefore said to them, "Truly, truly, I say to you, unless you eat the flesh of the Son of Man and drink His blood, you have no life in yourselves.
43推 6:54 "He who eats My flesh and drinks My blood has eternal life, and I will raise him up on the last day.
43推 6:55 "For My flesh is true food, and My blood is true drink.
43推 6:56 "He who eats My flesh and drinks My blood abides in Me, and I in him.
43推 6:57 "As the living Father sent Me, and I live because of the Father, so he who eats Me, he also shall live because of Me.
43推 6:58 "This is the bread which came down out of heaven; not as the fathers ate, and died, he who eats this bread shall live forever."
43推 6:59 These things He said in the synagogue, as He taught in Capernaum.
43推 6:60 Many therefore of His disciples, when they heard [this] said, "This is a difficult statement; who can listen to it?"
43推 6:61 But Jesus, conscious that His disciples grumbled at this, said to them, "Does this cause you to stumble?
43推 6:62 ["What] then if you should behold the Son of Man ascending where He was before?
43推 6:63 "It is the Spirit who gives life; the flesh profits nothing; the words that I have spoken to you are spirit and are life.
43推 6:64 "But there are some of you who do not believe." For Jesus knew from the beginning who they were who did not believe, and who it was that would betray Him.
43推 6:65 And He was saying, "For this reason I have said to you, that no one can come to Me, unless it has been granted him from the Father."
43推 6:66 As a result of this many of His disciples withdrew, and were not walking with Him anymore.
43推 6:67 Jesus said therefore to the twelve, "You do not want to go away also, do you?"
43推 6:68 Simon Peter answered Him, "Lord, to whom shall we go? You have words of eternal life.
43推 6:69 "And we have believed and have come to know that You are the Holy One of God."
43推 6:70 Jesus answered them, "Did I Myself not choose you, the twelve, and [ yet] one of you is a devil?"
43推 6:71 Now He meant Judas [the son] of Simon Iscariot, for he, one of the twelve, was going to betray Him.
43推 7:1 And after these things Jesus was walking in Galilee; for He was unwilling to walk in Judea, because the Jews were seeking to kill Him.
43推 7:2 Now the feast of the Jews, the Feast of Booths, was at hand.
43推 7:3 His brothers therefore said to Him, "Depart from here, and go into Judea, that Your disciples also may behold Your works which You are doing.
43推 7:4 "For no one does anything in secret, when he himself seeks to be [known] publicly. If You do these things, show Yourself to the world."
43推 7:5 For not even His brothers were believing in Him.
43推 7:6 Jesus therefore *said to them, "My time is not yet at hand, but your time is always opportune.
43推 7:7 "The world cannot hate you; but it hates Me because I testify of it, that its deeds are evil.
43推 7:8 "Go up to the feast yourselves; I do not go up to this feast because My time has not yet fully come."
43推 7:9 And having said these things to them, He stayed in Galilee.
43推 7:10 But when His brothers had gone up to the feast, then He Himself also went up, not publicly, but as it were, in secret.
43推 7:11 The Jews therefore were seeking Him at the feast, and were saying, " Where is He? "
43推 7:12 And there was much grumbling among the multitudes concerning Him; some were saying, "He is a good man"; others were saying, "No, on the contrary, He leads the multitude astray."
43推 7:13 Yet no one was speaking openly of Him for fear of the Jews.
43推 7:14 But when it was now the midst of the feast Jesus went up into the temple, and [began to] teach.
43推 7:15 The Jews therefore were marveling, saying, "How has this man become learned, having never been educated?"
43推 7:16 Jesus therefore answered them, and said, "My teaching is not Mine, but His who sent Me.
43推 7:17 "If any man is willing to do His will, he shall know of the teaching, whether it is of God, or [whether] I speak from Myself.
43推 7:18 "He who speaks from himself seeks his own glory; but He who is seeking the glory of the One who sent Him, He is true, and there is no unrighteousness in Him.
43推 7:19 "Did not Moses give you the Law, and [yet] none of you carries out the Law? Why do you seek to kill Me?"
43推 7:20 The multitude answered, "You have a demon! Who seeks to kill You?"
43推 7:21 Jesus answered and said to them, "I did one deed, and you all marvel.
43推 7:22 "On this account Moses has given you circumcision (not because it is from Moses, but from the fathers), and on [the] Sabbath you circumcise a man.
43推 7:23 "If a man receives circumcision on [the] Sabbath that the Law of Moses may not be broken, are you angry with Me because I made an entire man well on [the] Sabbath?
43推 7:24 "Do not judge according to appearance, but judge with righteous judgment."
43推 7:25 Therefore some of the people of Jerusalem were saying, "Is this not the man whom they are seeking to kill?
43推 7:26 "And look, He is speaking publicly, and they are saying nothing to Him. The rulers do not really know that this is the Christ, do they?
43推 7:27 "However, we know where this man is from; but whenever the Christ may come, no one knows where He is from."
43推 7:28 Jesus therefore cried out in the temple, teaching and saying, "You both know Me and know where I am from; and I have not come of Myself, but He who sent Me is true, whom you do not know.
43推 7:29 "I know Him; because I am from Him, and He sent Me."
43推 7:30 They were seeking therefore to seize Him; and no man laid his hand on Him, because His hour had not yet come.
43推 7:31 But many of the multitude believed in Him; and they were saying, "When the Christ shall come, He will not perform more signs than those which this man has, will He?"
43推 7:32 The Pharisees heard the multitude muttering these things about Him; and the chief priests and the Pharisees sent officers to seize Him.
43推 7:33 Jesus therefore said, "For a little while longer I am with you, then I go to Him who sent Me.
43推 7:34 "You shall seek Me, and shall not find Me; and where I am, you cannot come."
43推 7:35 The Jews therefore said to one another, "Where does this man intend to go that we shall not find Him? He is not intending to go to the Dispersion among the Greeks, and teach the Greeks, is He?
43推 7:36 "What is this statement that He said, 'You will seek Me, and will not find Me; and where I am, you cannot come'?"
43推 7:37 Now on the last day, the great [day] of the feast, Jesus stood and cried out, saying, "If any man is thirsty, let him come to Me and drink.
43推 7:38 "He who believes in Me, as the Scripture said, 'From his innermost being shall flow rivers of living water.'"
43推 7:39 But this He spoke of the Spirit, whom those who believed in Him were to receive; for the Spirit was not yet [given,] because Jesus was not yet glorified.
43推 7:40 [Some] of the multitude therefore, when they heard these words, were saying, "This certainly is the Prophet."
43推 7:41 Others were saying, "This is the Christ." Still others were saying, " Surely the Christ is not going to come from Galilee, is He?
43推 7:42 "Has not the Scripture said that the Christ comes from the offspring of David, and from Bethlehem, the village where David was?"
43推 7:43 So there arose a division in the multitude because of Him.
43推 7:44 And some of them wanted to seize Him, but no one laid hands on Him.
43推 7:45 The officers therefore came to the chief priests and Pharisees, and they said to them, "Why did you not bring Him?"
43推 7:46 The officers answered, "Never did a man speak the way this man speaks."
43推 7:47 The Pharisees therefore answered them, "You have not also been led astray, have you?
43推 7:48 "No one of the rulers or Pharisees has believed in Him, has he?
43推 7:49 "But this multitude which does not know the Law is accursed."
43推 7:50 Nicodemus *said to them (he who came to Him before, being one of them),
43推 7:51 "Our Law does not judge a man, unless it first hears from him and knows what he is doing, does it?"
43推 7:52 They answered and said to him, "You are not also from Galilee, are you? Search, and see that no prophet arises out of Galilee."
