43推 8:35 "And the slave does not remain in the house forever; the son does remain forever.
43推 8:36 "If therefore the Son shall make you free, you shall be free indeed.
43推 8:37 "I know that you are Abraham's offspring; yet you seek to kill Me, because My word has no place in you.
43推 8:38 "I speak the things which I have seen with [My] Father; therefore you also do the things which you heard from [your] father."
43推 8:39 They answered and said to Him, "Abraham is our father." Jesus *said to them, "If you are Abraham's children, do the deeds of Abraham.
43推 8:40 "But as it is, you are seeking to kill Me, a man who has told you the truth, which I heard from God; this Abraham did not do.
43推 8:41 "You are doing the deeds of your father." They said to Him, "We were not born of fornication; we have one Father, [even] God."
43推 8:42 Jesus said to them, "If God were your Father, you would love Me; for I proceeded forth and have come from God, for I have not even come on My own initiative, but He sent Me.
43推 8:43 "Why do you not understand what I am saying? [It is] because you cannot hear My word.
43推 8:44 "You are of [your] father the devil, and you want to do the desires of your father. He was a murderer from the beginning, and does not stand in the truth, because there is no truth in him. Whenever he speaks a lie, he speaks from his own [nature;] for he is a liar, and the father of lies.
43推 8:45 "But because I speak the truth, you do not believe Me.
43推 8:46 "Which one of you convicts Me of sin? If I speak truth, why do you not believe Me?
43推 8:47 "He who is of God hears the words of God; for this reason you do not hear [them,] because you are not of God."
43推 8:48 The Jews answered and said to Him, "Do we not say rightly that You are a Samaritan and have a demon?"
43推 8:49 Jesus answered, "I do not have a demon; but I honor My Father, and you dishonor Me.
43推 8:50 "But I do not seek My glory; there is One who seeks and judges.
43推 8:51 "Truly, truly, I say to you, if anyone keeps My word he shall never see death."
43推 8:52 The Jews said to Him, "Now we know that You have a demon. Abraham died, and the prophets [also]; and You say, 'If anyone keeps My word, he shall never taste of death.'
43推 8:53 "Surely You are not greater than our father Abraham, who died? The prophets died too; whom do You make Yourself out [to be]?"
43推 8:54 Jesus answered, "If I glorify Myself, My glory is nothing; it is My Father who glorifies Me, of whom you say, 'He is our God';
43推 8:55 and you have not come to know Him, but I know Him; and if I say that I do not know Him, I shall be a liar like you, but I do know Him, and keep His word.
43推 8:56 "Your father Abraham rejoiced to see My day, and he saw [it] and was glad."
43推 8:57 The Jews therefore said to Him, "You are not yet fifty years old, and have You seen Abraham?"
43推 8:58 Jesus said to them, "Truly, truly, I say to you, before Abraham was born, I am."
43推 8:59 Therefore they picked up stones to throw at Him; but Jesus hid Himself, and went out of the temple.
43推 9:1 And as He passed by, He saw a man blind from birth.
43推 9:2 And His disciples asked Him, saying, "Rabbi, who sinned, this man or his parents, that he should be born blind?"
43推 9:3 Jesus answered, "[It was] neither [that] this man sinned, nor his parents; but [it was] in order that the works of God might be displayed in him.
43推 9:4 "We must work the works of Him who sent Me, as long as it is day; night is coming, when no man can work.
43推 9:5 "While I am in the world, I am the light of the world."
43推 9:6 When He had said this, He spat on the ground, and made clay of the spittle, and applied the clay to his eyes,
43推 9:7 and said to him, "Go, wash in the pool of Siloam" (which is translated, Sent). And so he went away and washed, and came [back] seeing.
43推 9:8 The neighbors therefore, and those who previously saw him as a beggar, were saying, "Is not this the one who used to sit and beg?"
43推 9:9 Others were saying, "This is he," [still] others were saying, "No, but he is like him." He kept saying, "I am the one."
43推 9:10 Therefore they were saying to him, "How then were your eyes opened?"
43推 9:11 He answered, "The man who is called Jesus made clay, and anointed my eyes, and said to me, 'Go to Siloam, and wash'; so I went away and washed, and I received sight."
43推 9:12 And they said to him, "Where is He?" He *said, "I do not know."
43推 9:13 They *brought to the Pharisees him who was formerly blind.
43推 9:14 Now it was a Sabbath on the day when Jesus made the clay, and opened his eyes.
43推 9:15 Again, therefore, the Pharisees also were asking him how he received his sight. And he said to them, "He applied clay to my eyes, and I washed, and I see."
43推 9:16 Therefore some of the Pharisees were saying, "This man is not from God, because He does not keep the Sabbath." But others were saying, "How can a man who is a sinner perform such signs?" And there was a division among them.
43推 9:17 They *said therefore to the blind man again, "What do you say about Him, since He opened your eyes?" And he said, "He is a prophet."
43推 9:18 The Jews therefore did not believe [it] of him, that he had been blind, and had received sight, until they called the parents of the very one who had received his sight,
43推 9:19 and questioned them, saying, "Is this your son, who you say was born blind? Then how does he now see?"
43推 9:20 His parents answered them and said, "We know that this is our son, and that he was born blind;
43推 9:21 but how he now sees, we do not know; or who opened his eyes, we do not know. Ask him; he is of age, he shall speak for himself. "
43推 9:22 His parents said this because they were afraid of the Jews; for the Jews had already agreed, that if anyone should confess Him to be Christ, he should be put out of the synagogue.
43推 9:23 For this reason his parents said, "He is of age; ask him."
43推 9:24 So a second time they called the man who had been blind, and said to him, "Give glory to God; we know that this man is a sinner."
43推 9:25 He therefore answered, "Whether He is a sinner, I do not know; one thing I do know, that, whereas I was blind, now I see."
43推 9:26 They said therefore to him, "What did He do to you? How did He open your eyes?"
43推 9:27 He answered them, "I told you already, and you did not listen; why do you want to hear [it] again? You do not want to become His disciples too, do you?"
43推 9:28 And they reviled him, and said, "You are His disciple, but we are disciples of Moses.
43推 9:29 "We know that God has spoken to Moses; but as for this man, we do not know where He is from."
43推 9:30 The man answered and said to them, "Well, here is an amazing thing, that you do not know where He is from, and [yet] He opened my eyes.
43推 9:31 "We know that God does not hear sinners; but if anyone is God-fearing, and does His will, He hears him.
43推 9:32 "Since the beginning of time it has never been heard that anyone opened the eyes of a person born blind.
43推 9:33 "If this man were not from God, He could do nothing."
43推 9:34 They answered and said to him, "You were born entirely in sins, and are you teaching us?" And they put him out.
43推 9:35 Jesus heard that they had put him out; and finding him, He said, " Do you believe in the Son of Man? "
43推 9:36 He answered and said, "And who is He, Lord, that I may believe in Him?"
43推 9:37 Jesus said to him, "You have both seen Him, and He is the one who is talking with you."
43推 9:38 And he said, "Lord, I believe." And he worshiped Him.
43推 9:39 And Jesus said, "For judgment I came into this world, that those who do not see may see; and that those who see may become blind."
43推 9:40 Those of the Pharisees who were with Him heard these things, and said to Him, "We are not blind too, are we?"
43推 9:41 Jesus said to them, "If you were blind, you would have no sin; but since you say, 'We see,' your sin remains.
43推 10:1 "Truly, truly, I say to you, he who does not enter by the door into the fold of the sheep, but climbs up some other way, he is a thief and a robber.
43推 10:2 "But he who enters by the door is a shepherd of the sheep.
43推 10:3 "To him the doorkeeper opens, and the sheep hear his voice, and he calls his own sheep by name, and leads them out.
43推 10:4 "When he puts forth all his own, he goes before them, and the sheep follow him because they know his voice.
43推 10:5 "And a stranger they simply will not follow, but will flee from him, because they do not know the voice of strangers."
43推 10:6 This figure of speech Jesus spoke to them, but they did not understand what those things were which He had been saying to them.
43推 10:7 Jesus therefore said to them again, "Truly, truly, I say to you, I am the door of the sheep.
43推 10:8 "All who came before Me are thieves and robbers, but the sheep did not hear them.
43推 10:9 "I am the door; if anyone enters through Me, he shall be saved, and shall go in and out, and find pasture.
43推 10:10 "The thief comes only to steal, and kill, and destroy; I came that they might have life, and might have [it] abundantly.
43推 10:11 "I am the good shepherd; the good shepherd lays down His life for the sheep.
43推 10:12 "He who is a hireling, and not a shepherd, who is not the owner of the sheep, beholds the wolf coming, and leaves the sheep, and flees, and the wolf snatches them, and scatters [them.]
43推 10:13 ["He flees] because he is a hireling, and is not concerned about the sheep.
43推 10:14 "I am the good shepherd; and I know My own, and My own know Me,
43推 10:15 even as the Father knows Me and I know the Father; and I lay down My life for the sheep.
43推 10:16 "And I have other sheep, which are not of this fold; I must bring them also, and they shall hear My voice; and they shall become one flock [with] one shepherd.
43推 10:17 "For this reason the Father loves Me, because I lay down My life that I may take it again.
43推 10:18 "No one has taken it away from Me, but I lay it down on My own initiative. I have authority to lay it down, and I have authority to take it up again. This commandment I received from My Father."
43推 10:19 There arose a division again among the Jews because of these words.
43推 10:20 And many of them were saying, "He has a demon and is insane. Why do you listen to Him?"
43推 10:21 Others were saying, "These are not the sayings of one demon-possessed. A demon cannot open the eyes of the blind, can he?"
43推 10:22 At that time the Feast of the Dedication took place at Jerusalem;
43推 10:23 it was winter, and Jesus was walking in the temple in the portico of Solomon.
43推 10:24 The Jews therefore gathered around Him, and were saying to Him, "How long will You keep us in suspense? If You are the Christ, tell us plainly."
43推 10:25 Jesus answered them, "I told you, and you do not believe; the works that I do in My Father's name, these bear witness of Me.
43推 10:26 "But you do not believe, because you are not of My sheep.
43推 10:27 "My sheep hear My voice, and I know them, and they follow Me;
43推 10:28 and I give eternal life to them, and they shall never perish; and no one shall snatch them out of My hand.
43推 10:29 "My Father, who has given [them] to Me, is greater than all; and no one is able to snatch [them] out of the Father's hand.
43推 10:30 "I and the Father are one."
43推 10:31 The Jews took up stones again to stone Him.
43推 10:32 Jesus answered them, "I showed you many good works from the Father; for which of them are you stoning Me?"
43推 10:33 The Jews answered Him, "For a good work we do not stone You, but for blasphemy; and because You, being a man, make Yourself out [to be] God."
43推 10:34 Jesus answered them, "Has it not been written in your Law, 'I SAID, YOU ARE GODS'?
43推 10:35 "If he called them gods, to whom the word of God came (and the Scripture cannot be broken),
43推 10:36 do you say of Him, whom the Father sanctified and sent into the world, 'You are blaspheming,' because I said, 'I am the Son of God'?
43推 10:37 "If I do not do the works of My Father, do not believe Me;
43推 10:38 but if I do them, though you do not believe Me, believe the works, that you may know and understand that the Father is in Me, and I in the Father. "
43推 10:39 Therefore they were seeking again to seize Him, and He eluded their grasp.
43推 10:40 And He went away again beyond the Jordan to the place where John was first baptizing, and He was staying there.
43推 10:41 And many came to Him and were saying, "While John performed no sign, yet everything John said about this man was true."
43推 10:42 And many believed in Him there.
43推 11:1 Now a certain man was sick, Lazarus of Bethany, the village of Mary and her sister Martha.
43推 11:2 And it was the Mary who anointed the Lord with ointment, and wiped His feet with her hair, whose brother Lazarus was sick.
43推 11:3 The sisters therefore sent to Him, saying, "Lord, behold, he whom You love is sick."
43推 11:4 But when Jesus heard it, He said, "This sickness is not unto death, but for the glory of God, that the Son of God may be glorified by it."
43推 11:5 Now Jesus loved Martha, and her sister, and Lazarus.
43推 11:6 When therefore He heard that he was sick, He stayed then two days [ longer] in the place where He was.
43推 11:7 Then after this He *said to the disciples, "Let us go to Judea again."
43推 11:8 The disciples *said to Him, "Rabbi, the Jews were just now seeking to stone You, and are You going there again?"
43推 11:9 Jesus answered, "Are there not twelve hours in the day? If anyone walks in the day, he does not stumble, because he sees the light of this world.
43推 11:10 "But if anyone walks in the night, he stumbles, because the light is not in him."
43推 11:11 This He said, and after that He *said to them, "Our friend Lazarus has fallen asleep; but I go, that I may awaken him out of sleep."
43推 11:12 The disciples therefore said to Him, "Lord, if he has fallen asleep, he will recover."
43推 11:13 Now Jesus had spoken of his death, but they thought that He was speaking of literal sleep.
43推 11:14 Then Jesus therefore said to them plainly, "Lazarus is dead,
43推 11:15 and I am glad for your sakes that I was not there, so that you may believe; but let us go to him. "
43推 11:16 Thomas therefore, who is called Didymus, said to [his] fellow disciples, "Let us also go, that we may die with Him."
43推 11:17 So when Jesus came, He found that he had already been in the tomb four days.
43推 11:18 Now Bethany was near Jerusalem, about two miles off;
43推 11:19 and many of the Jews had come to Martha and Mary, to console them concerning [their] brother.
43推 11:20 Martha therefore, when she heard that Jesus was coming, went to meet Him; but Mary still sat in the house.
43推 11:21 Martha therefore said to Jesus, "Lord, if You had been here, my brother would not have died.
43推 11:22 "Even now I know that whatever You ask of God, God will give You."
43推 11:23 Jesus *said to her, "Your brother shall rise again."
43推 11:24 Martha *said to Him, "I know that he will rise again in the resurrection on the last day."
43推 11:25 Jesus said to her, "I am the resurrection and the life; he who believes in Me shall live even if he dies,
43推 11:26 and everyone who lives and believes in Me shall never die. Do you believe this? "
43推 11:27 She *said to Him, "Yes, Lord; I have believed that You are the Christ, the Son of God, [even] He who comes into the world."
43推 11:28 And when she had said this, she went away, and called Mary her sister, saying secretly, "The Teacher is here, and is calling for you."
43推 11:29 And when she heard it, she *arose quickly, and was coming to Him.
43推 11:30 Now Jesus had not yet come into the village, but was still in the place where Martha met Him.
43推 11:31 The Jews then who were with her in the house, and consoling her, when they saw that Mary rose up quickly and went out, followed her, supposing that she was going to the tomb to weep there.
43推 11:32 Therefore, when Mary came where Jesus was, she saw Him, and fell at His feet, saying to Him, "Lord, if You had been here, my brother would not have died."
43推 11:33 When Jesus therefore saw her weeping, and the Jews who came with her, [also] weeping, He was deeply moved in spirit, and was troubled,
43推 11:34 and said, "Where have you laid him?" They *said to Him, "Lord, come and see."
43推 11:35 Jesus wept.
43推 11:36 And so the Jews were saying, "Behold how He loved him!"
43推 11:37 But some of them said, "Could not this man, who opened the eyes of him who was blind, have kept this man also from dying?"
43推 11:38 Jesus therefore again being deeply moved within, *came to the tomb. Now it was a cave, and a stone was lying against it.
43推 11:39 Jesus *said, "Remove the stone." Martha, the sister of the deceased, *said to Him, "Lord, by this time there will be a stench, for he has been [dead] four days."
43推 11:40 Jesus *said to her, "Did I not say to you, if you believe, you will see the glory of God?"
43推 11:41 And so they removed the stone. And Jesus raised His eyes, and said, "Father, I thank Thee that Thou heardest Me.
43推 11:42 "And I knew that Thou hearest Me always; but because of the people standing around I said it, that they may believe that Thou didst send Me."
43推 11:43 And when He had said these things, He cried out with a loud voice, " Lazarus, come forth. "
43推 11:44 He who had died came forth, bound hand and foot with wrappings; and his face was wrapped around with a cloth. Jesus *said to them, "Unbind him, and let him go."
43推 11:45 Many therefore of the Jews, who had come to Mary and beheld what He had done, believed in Him.
43推 11:46 But some of them went away to the Pharisees, and told them the things which Jesus had done.
43推 11:47 Therefore the chief priests and the Pharisees convened a council, and were saying, "What are we doing? For this man is performing many signs.
43推 11:48 "If we let Him [go on] like this, all men will believe in Him, and the Romans will come and take away both our place and our nation."
43推 11:49 But a certain one of them, Caiaphas, who was high priest that year, said to them, "You know nothing at all,
43推 11:50 nor do you take into account that it is expedient for you that one man should die for the people, and that the whole nation should not perish. "
43推 11:51 Now this he did not say on his own initiative; but being high priest that year, he prophesied that Jesus was going to die for the nation,
43推 11:52 and not for the nation only, but that He might also gather together into one the children of God who are scattered abroad.
43推 11:53 So from that day on they planned together to kill Him.
43推 11:54 Jesus therefore no longer continued to walk publicly among the Jews, but went away from there to the country near the wilderness, into a city called Ephraim; and there He stayed with the disciples.
43推 11:55 Now the Passover of the Jews was at hand, and many went up to Jerusalem out of the country before the Passover, to purify themselves.
43推 11:56 Therefore they were seeking for Jesus, and were saying to one another, as they stood in the temple, "What do you think; that He will not come to the feast at all?"
43推 11:57 Now the chief priests and the Pharisees had given orders that if anyone knew where He was, he should report it, that they might seize Him.
43推 12:1 Jesus, therefore, six days before the Passover, came to Bethany where Lazarus was, whom Jesus had raised from the dead.
43推 12:2 So they made Him a supper there, and Martha was serving; but Lazarus was one of those reclining [at the table] with Him.
43推 12:3 Mary therefore took a pound of very costly perfume of pure nard, and anointed the feet of Jesus, and wiped His feet with her hair; and the house was filled with the fragrance of the perfume.
43推 12:4 But Judas Iscariot, one of His disciples, who was intending to betray Him, *said,
43推 12:5 "Why was this perfume not sold for three hundred denarii, and given to poor [people]?"
43推 12:6 Now he said this, not because he was concerned about the poor, but because he was a thief, and as he had the money box, he used to pilfer what was put into it.
43推 12:7 Jesus therefore said, "Let her alone, in order that she may keep it for the day of My burial.
43推 12:8 "For the poor you always have with you, but you do not always have Me."
43推 12:9 The great multitude therefore of the Jews learned that He was there; and they came, not for Jesus' sake only, but that they might also see Lazarus, whom He raised from the dead.
43推 12:10 But the chief priests took counsel that they might put Lazarus to death also;
43推 12:11 because on account of him many of the Jews were going away, and were believing in Jesus.
43推 12:12 On the next day the great multitude who had come to the feast, when they heard that Jesus was coming to Jerusalem,
43推 12:13 took the branches of the palm trees, and went out to meet Him, and [began] to cry out, "Hosanna! BLESSED IS HE WHO COMES IN THE NAME OF THE LORD, even the King of Israel."
43推 12:14 And Jesus, finding a young donkey, sat on it; as it is written,
43推 12:15 "FEAR NOT, DAUGHTER OF ZION; BEHOLD, YOUR KING IS COMING, SEATED ON A Donkey's COLT."
43推 12:16 These things His disciples did not understand at the first; but when Jesus was glorified, then they remembered that these things were written of Him, and that they had done these things to Him.
43推 12:17 And so the multitude who were with Him when He called Lazarus out of the tomb, and raised him from the dead, were bearing Him witness.
43推 12:18 For this cause also the multitude went and met Him, because they heard that He had performed this sign.
43推 12:19 The Pharisees therefore said to one another, "You see that you are not doing any good; look, the world has gone after Him."
43推 12:20 Now there were certain Greeks among those who were going up to worship at the feast;
43推 12:21 these therefore came to Philip, who was from Bethsaida of Galilee, and [began to] ask him, saying, "Sir, we wish to see Jesus."
43推 12:22 Philip *came and *told Andrew; Andrew and Philip *came, and they * told Jesus.
43推 12:23 And Jesus *answered them, saying, "The hour has come for the Son of Man to be glorified.
43推 12:24 "Truly, truly, I say to you, unless a grain of wheat falls into the earth and dies, it remains by itself alone; but if it dies, it bears much fruit.
43推 12:25 "He who loves his life loses it; and he who hates his life in this world shall keep it to life eternal.
43推 12:26 "If anyone serves Me, let him follow Me; and where I am, there shall My servant also be; if anyone serves Me, the Father will honor him.
43推 12:27 "Now My soul has become troubled; and what shall I say, 'Father, save Me from this hour'? But for this purpose I came to this hour.
43推 12:28 "Father, glorify Thy name." There came therefore a voice out of heaven "I have both glorified it, and will glorify it again."
43推 12:29 The multitude therefore, who stood by and heard it, were saying that it had thundered; others were saying, "An angel has spoken to Him."
43推 12:30 Jesus answered and said, "This voice has not come for My sake, but for your sakes.
43推 12:31 "Now judgment is upon this world; now the ruler of this world shall be cast out.
43推 12:32 "And I, if I be lifted up from the earth, will draw all men to Myself."
43推 12:33 But He was saying this to indicate the kind of death by which He was to die.
43推 12:34 The multitude therefore answered Him, "We have heard out of the Law that the Christ is to remain forever; and how can You say, 'The Son of Man must be lifted up'? Who is this Son of Man?"
43推 12:35 Jesus therefore said to them, "For a little while longer the light is among you. Walk while you have the light, that darkness may not overtake you; he who walks in the darkness does not know where he goes.
43推 12:36 "While you have the light, believe in the light, in order that you may become sons of light." These things Jesus spoke, and He departed and hid Himself from them.
43推 12:37 But though He had performed so many signs before them, [yet] they were not believing in Him;
43推 12:38 that the word of Isaiah the prophet might be fulfilled, which he spoke, "LORD, WHO HAS BELIEVED OUR REPORT? AND TO WHOM HAS THE ARM OF THE LORD BEEN REVEALED?"
43推 12:39 For this cause they could not believe, for Isaiah said again,
43推 12:40 "HE HAS BLINDED THEIR EYES, AND HE HARDENED THEIR HEART; LEST THEY SEE WITH THEIR EYES, AND PERCEIVE WITH THEIR HEART, AND BE CONVERTED, AND I HEAL THEM."
43推 12:41 These things Isaiah said, because he saw His glory, and he spoke of Him.
43推 12:42 Nevertheless many even of the rulers believed in Him, but because of the Pharisees they were not confessing [Him,] lest they should be put out of the synagogue;
43推 12:43 for they loved the approval of men rather than the approval of God.
43推 12:44 And Jesus cried out and said, "He who believes in Me does not believe in Me, but in Him who sent Me.
43推 12:45 "And he who beholds Me beholds the One who sent Me.
43推 12:46 "I have come [as] light into the world, that everyone who believes in Me may not remain in darkness.
43推 12:47 "And if anyone hears My sayings, and does not keep them, I do not judge him; for I did not come to judge the world, but to save the world.
43推 12:48 "He who rejects Me, and does not receive My sayings, has one who judges him; the word I spoke is what will judge him at the last day.
43推 12:49 "For I did not speak on My own initiative, but the Father Himself who sent Me has given Me commandment, what to say, and what to speak.
43推 12:50 "And I know that His commandment is eternal life; therefore the things I speak, I speak just as the Father has told Me."
43推 13:1 Now before the Feast of the Passover, Jesus knowing that His hour had come that He should depart out of this world to the Father, having loved His own who were in the world, He loved them to the end.
43推 13:2 And during supper, the devil having already put into the heart of Judas Iscariot, [the son] of Simon, to betray Him,
43推 13:3 [Jesus,] knowing that the Father had given all things into His hands, and that He had come forth from God, and was going back to God,
43推 13:4 *rose from supper, and *laid aside His garments; and taking a towel, He girded Himself about.
43推 13:5 Then He *poured water into the basin, and began to wash the disciples' feet, and to wipe them with the towel with which He was girded.
43推 13:6 And so He *came to Simon Peter. He *said to Him, "Lord, do You wash my feet?"
43推 13:7 Jesus answered and said to him, "What I do you do not realize now, but you shall understand hereafter."
43推 13:8 Peter *said to Him, "Never shall You wash my feet!" Jesus answered him, "If I do not wash you, you have no part with Me."
43推 13:9 Simon Peter *said to Him, "Lord, not my feet only, but also my hands and my head."
43推 13:10 Jesus *said to him, "He who has bathed needs only to wash his feet, but is completely clean; and you are clean, but not all [of you.]"
43推 13:11 For He knew the one who was betraying Him; for this reason He said, "Not all of you are clean."
43推 13:12 And so when He had washed their feet, and taken His garments, and reclined [at the table] again, He said to them, "Do you know what I have done to you?
43推 13:13 "You call Me Teacher and Lord; and you are right, for [so] I am.
43推 13:14 "If I then, the Lord and the Teacher, washed your feet, you also ought to wash one another's feet.
43推 13:15 "For I gave you an example that you also should do as I did to you.
43推 13:16 "Truly, truly, I say to you, a slave is not greater than his master; neither [is] one who is sent greater than the one who sent him.
43推 13:17 "If you know these things, you are blessed if you do them.
43推 13:18 "I do not speak of all of you. I know the ones I have chosen; but [ it is] that the Scripture may be fulfilled, 'HE WHO EATS MY BREAD HAS LIFTED UP HIS HEEL AGAINST ME.'
43推 13:19 "From now on I am telling you before [it] comes to pass, so that when it does occur, you may believe that I am [He.]
43推 13:20 "Truly, truly, I say to you, he who receives whomever I send receives Me; and he who receives Me receives Him who sent Me."
43推 13:21 When Jesus had said this, He became troubled in spirit, and testified, and said, "Truly, truly, I say to you, that one of you will betray Me."
43推 13:22 The disciples [began] looking at one another, at a loss [to know] of which one He was speaking.
43推 13:23 There was reclining on Jesus' breast one of His disciples, whom Jesus loved.
43推 13:24 Simon Peter therefore *gestured to him, and *said to him, "Tell [us] who it is of whom He is speaking."
43推 13:25 He, leaning back thus on Jesus' breast, *said to Him, "Lord, who is it?"
43推 13:26 Jesus therefore *answered, "That is the one for whom I shall dip the morsel and give it to him." So when He had dipped the morsel, He *took and *gave it to Judas, [the son] of Simon Iscariot.
43推 13:27 And after the morsel, Satan then entered into him. Jesus therefore *said to him, "What you do, do quickly."
43推 13:28 Now no one of those reclining [at the table] knew for what purpose He had said this to him.
43推 13:29 For some were supposing, because Judas had the money box, that Jesus was saying to him, "Buy the things we have need of for the feast"; or else, that he should give something to the poor.
43推 13:30 And so after receiving the morsel he went out immediately; and it was night.
43推 13:31 When therefore he had gone out, Jesus *said, "Now is the Son of Man glorified, and God is glorified in Him;
43推 13:32 if God is glorified in Him, God will also glorify Him in Himself, and will glorify Him immediately.
43推 13:33 "Little children, I am with you a little while longer. You shall seek Me; and as I said to the Jews, I now say to you also, 'Where I am going, you cannot come.'
43推 13:34 "A new commandment I give to you, that you love one another, even as I have loved you, that you also love one another.
43推 13:35 "By this all men will know that you are My disciples, if you have love for one another."
43推 13:36 Simon Peter *said to Him, "Lord, where are You going?" Jesus answered, "Where I go, you cannot follow Me now; but you shall follow later."
43推 13:37 Peter *said to Him, "Lord, why can I not follow You right now? I will lay down my life for You."
43推 13:38 Jesus *answered, "Will you lay down your life for Me? Truly, truly, I say to you, a cock shall not crow, until you deny Me three times.
43推 14:1 "Let not your heart be troubled; believe in God, believe also in Me.
43推 14:2 "In My Father's house are many dwelling places; if it were not so, I would have told you; for I go to prepare a place for you.
43推 14:3 "And if I go and prepare a place for you, I will come again, and receive you to Myself; that where I am, [there] you may be also.
43推 14:4 "And you know the way where I am going."
43推 14:5 Thomas *said to Him, "Lord, we do not know where You are going, how do we know the way?"
43推 14:6 Jesus *said to him, "I am the way, and the truth, and the life; no one comes to the Father, but through Me.
43推 14:7 "If you had known Me, you would have known My Father also; from now on you know Him, and have seen Him."
43推 14:8 Philip *said to Him, "Lord, show us the Father, and it is enough for us."
43推 14:9 Jesus *said to him, "Have I been so long with you, and [yet] you have not come to know Me, Philip? He who has seen Me has seen the Father; how do you say, 'Show us the Father'?
43推 14:10 "Do you not believe that I am in the Father, and the Father is in Me? The words that I say to you I do not speak on My own initiative, but the Father abiding in Me does His works.
43推 14:11 "Believe Me that I am in the Father, and the Father in Me; otherwise believe on account of the works themselves.
43推 14:12 "Truly, truly, I say to you, he who believes in Me, the works that I do shall he do also; and greater [works] than these shall he do; because I go to the Father.
43推 14:13 "And whatever you ask in My name, that will I do, that the Father may be glorified in the Son.
43推 14:14 "If you ask Me anything in My name, I will do [it.]
43推 14:15 "If you love Me, you will keep My commandments.
43推 14:16 "And I will ask the Father, and He will give you another Helper, that He may be with you forever;
43推 14:17 [that is] the Spirit of truth, whom the world cannot receive, because it does not behold Him or know Him, [but] you know Him because He abides with you, and will be in you.
43推 14:18 "I will not leave you as orphans; I will come to you.
43推 14:19 "After a little while the world will behold Me no more; but you [will] behold Me; because I live, you shall live also.
43推 14:20 "In that day you shall know that I am in My Father, and you in Me, and I in you.
43推 14:21 "He who has My commandments and keeps them, he it is who loves Me; and he who loves Me shall be loved by My Father, and I will love him, and will disclose Myself to him."
43推 14:22 Judas (not Iscariot) *said to Him, "Lord, what then has happened that You are going to disclose Yourself to us, and not to the world?"
43推 14:23 Jesus answered and said to him, "If anyone loves Me, he will keep My word; and My Father will love him, and We will come to him, and make Our abode with him.
43推 14:24 "He who does not love Me does not keep My words; and the word which you hear is not Mine, but the Father's who sent Me.
43推 14:25 "These things I have spoken to you, while abiding with you.
43推 14:26 "But the Helper, the Holy Spirit, whom the Father will send in My name, He will teach you all things, and bring to your remembrance all that I said to you.
43推 14:27 "Peace I leave with you; My peace I give to you; not as the world gives, do I give to you. Let not your heart be troubled, nor let it be fearful.
43推 14:28 "You heard that I said to you, 'I go away, and I will come to you.' If you loved Me, you would have rejoiced, because I go to the Father; for the Father is greater than I.
43推 14:29 "And now I have told you before it comes to pass, that when it comes to pass, you may believe.
43推 14:30 "I will not speak much more with you, for the ruler of the world is coming, and he has nothing in Me;
43推 14:31 but that the world may know that I love the Father, and as the Father gave Me commandment, even so I do. Arise, let us go from here.
43推 15:1 "I am the true vine, and My Father is the vinedresser.
43推 15:2 "Every branch in Me that does not bear fruit, He takes away; and every [branch] that bears fruit, He prunes it, that it may bear more fruit.
43推 15:3 "You are already clean because of the word which I have spoken to you.
43推 15:4 "Abide in Me, and I in you. As the branch cannot bear fruit of itself, unless it abides in the vine, so neither [can] you, unless you abide in Me.
43推 15:5 "I am the vine, you are the branches; he who abides in Me, and I in him, he bears much fruit; for apart from Me you can do nothing.
43推 15:6 "If anyone does not abide in Me, he is thrown away as a branch, and dries up; and they gather them, and cast them into the fire, and they are burned.
43推 15:7 "If you abide in Me, and My words abide in you, ask whatever you wish, and it shall be done for you.
43推 15:8 "By this is My Father glorified, that you bear much fruit, and [so] prove to be My disciples.
43推 15:9 "Just as the Father has loved Me, I have also loved you; abide in My love.
43推 15:10 "If you keep My commandments, you will abide in My love; just as I have kept My Father's commandments, and abide in His love.
43推 15:11 "These things I have spoken to you, that My joy may be in you, and [that] your joy may be made full.
43推 15:12 "This is My commandment, that you love one another, just as I have loved you.
43推 15:13 "Greater love has no one than this, that one lay down his life for his friends.
43推 15:14 "You are My friends, if you do what I command you.
43推 15:15 "No longer do I call you slaves, for the slave does not know what his master is doing; but I have called you friends, for all things that I have heard from My Father I have made known to you.
43推 15:16 "You did not choose Me, but I chose you, and appointed you, that you should go and bear fruit, and [that] your fruit should remain, that whatever you ask of the Father in My name, He may give to you.
43推 15:17 "This I command you, that you love one another.
43推 15:18 "If the world hates you, you know that it has hated Me before [it hated] you.
43推 15:19 "If you were of the world, the world would love its own; but because you are not of the world, but I chose you out of the world, therefore the world hates you.
43推 15:20 "Remember the word that I said to you, 'A slave is not greater than his master.' If they persecuted Me, they will also persecute you; if they kept My word, they will keep yours also.
43推 15:21 "But all these things they will do to you for My name's sake, because they do not know the One who sent Me.
43推 15:22 "If I had not come and spoken to them, they would not have sin, but now they have no excuse for their sin.
43推 15:23 "He who hates Me hates My Father also.
43推 15:24 "If I had not done among them the works which no one else did, they would not have sin; but now they have both seen and hated Me and My Father as well.
43推 15:25 "But [they have done this] in order that the word may be fulfilled that is written in their Law, 'THEY HATED ME WITHOUT A CAUSE.'
43推 15:26 "When the Helper comes, whom I will send to you from the Father, [ that is] the Spirit of truth, who proceeds from the Father, He will bear witness of Me,
43推 15:27 and you [will] bear witness also, because you have been with Me from the beginning.
43推 16:1 "These things I have spoken to you, that you may be kept from stumbling.
43推 16:2 "They will make you outcasts from the synagogue, but an hour is coming for everyone who kills you to think that he is offering service to God.
43推 16:3 "And these things they will do, because they have not known the Father, or Me.
43推 16:4 "But these things I have spoken to you, that when their hour comes, you may remember that I told you of them. And these things I did not say to you at the beginning, because I was with you.
43推 16:5 "But now I am going to Him who sent Me; and none of you asks Me, 'Where are You going?'
43推 16:6 "But because I have said these things to you, sorrow has filled your heart.
43推 16:7 "But I tell you the truth, it is to your advantage that I go away; for if I do not go away, the Helper shall not come to you; but if I go, I will send Him to you.
43推 16:8 "And He, when He comes, will convict the world concerning sin, and righteousness, and judgment;
43推 16:9 concerning sin, because they do not believe in Me;
43推 16:10 and concerning righteousness, because I go to the Father, and you no longer behold Me;
43推 16:11 and concerning judgment, because the ruler of this world has been judged.
43推 16:12 "I have many more things to say to you, but you cannot bear [them] now.
43推 16:13 "But when He, the Spirit of truth, comes, He will guide you into all the truth; for He will not speak on His own initiative, but whatever He hears, He will speak; and He will disclose to you what is to come.
43推 16:14 "He shall glorify Me; for He shall take of Mine, and shall disclose [it] to you.
43推 16:15 "All things that the Father has are Mine; therefore I said, that He takes of Mine, and will disclose [it] to you.
43推 16:16 "A little while, and you will no longer behold Me; and again a little while, and you will see Me."
43推 16:17 [Some] of His disciples therefore said to one another, "What is this thing He is telling us, 'A little while, and you will not behold Me; and again a little while, and you will see Me'; and, 'because I go to the Father'?"
43推 16:18 And so they were saying, "What is this that He says, 'A little while'? We do not know what He is talking about."
43推 16:19 Jesus knew that they wished to question Him, and He said to them, " Are you deliberating together about this, that I said, 'A little while, and you will not behold Me, and again a little while, and you will see Me'?
43推 16:20 "Truly, truly, I say to you, that you will weep and lament, but the world will rejoice; you will be sorrowful, but your sorrow will be turned to joy.
43推 16:21 "Whenever a woman is in travail she has sorrow, because her hour has come; but when she gives birth to the child, she remembers the anguish no more, for joy that a child has been born into the world.
43推 16:22 "Therefore you too now have sorrow; but I will see you again, and your heart will rejoice, and no one takes your joy away from you.
43推 16:23 "And in that day you will ask Me no question. Truly, truly, I say to you, if you shall ask the Father for anything, He will give it to you in My name.
43推 16:24 "Until now you have asked for nothing in My name; ask, and you will receive, that your joy may be made full.
43推 16:25 "These things I have spoken to you in figurative language; an hour is coming when I will speak no more to you in figurative language, but will tell you plainly of the Father.
43推 16:26 "In that day you will ask in My name, and I do not say to you that I will request the Father on your behalf;
43推 16:27 for the Father Himself loves you, because you have loved Me, and have believed that I came forth from the Father.
43推 16:28 "I came forth from the Father, and have come into the world; I am leaving the world again, and going to the Father."
43推 16:29 His disciples *said, "Lo, now You are speaking plainly, and are not using a figure of speech.
43推 16:30 "Now we know that You know all things, and have no need for anyone to question You; by this we believe that You came from God."
43推 16:31 Jesus answered them, "Do you now believe?
43推 16:32 "Behold, an hour is coming, and has [already] come, for you to be scattered, each to his own [home,] and to leave Me alone; and [yet] I am not alone, because the Father is with Me.
43推 16:33 "These things I have spoken to you, that in Me you may have peace. In the world you have tribulation, but take courage; I have overcome the world."
43推 17:1 These things Jesus spoke; and lifting up His eyes to heaven, He said, "Father, the hour has come; glorify Thy Son, that the Son may glorify Thee,
43推 17:2 even as Thou gavest Him authority over all mankind, that to all whom Thou hast given Him, He may give eternal life.
43推 17:3 "And this is eternal life, that they may know Thee, the only true God, and Jesus Christ whom Thou hast sent.
43推 17:4 "I glorified Thee on the earth, having accomplished the work which Thou hast given Me to do.
43推 17:5 "And now, glorify Thou Me together with Thyself, Father, with the glory which I had with Thee before the world was.
43推 17:6 "I manifested Thy name to the men whom Thou gavest Me out of the world; Thine they were, and Thou gavest them to Me, and they have kept Thy word.
43推 17:7 "Now they have come to know that everything Thou hast given Me is from Thee;
43推 17:8 for the words which Thou gavest Me I have given to them; and they received [them,] and truly understood that I came forth from Thee, and they believed that Thou didst send Me.
43推 17:9 "I ask on their behalf; I do not ask on behalf of the world, but of those whom Thou hast given Me; for they are Thine;
43推 17:10 and all things that are Mine are Thine, and Thine are Mine; and I have been glorified in them.
43推 17:11 "And I am no more in the world; and [yet] they themselves are in the world, and I come to Thee. Holy Father, keep them in Thy name, [the name] which Thou hast given Me, that they may be one, even as We [are.]
43推 17:12 "While I was with them, I was keeping them in Thy name which Thou hast given Me; and I guarded them, and not one of them perished but the son of perdition, that the Scripture might be fulfilled.
43推 17:13 "But now I come to Thee; and these things I speak in the world, that they may have My joy made full in themselves.
43推 17:14 "I have given them Thy word; and the world has hated them, because they are not of the world, even as I am not of the world.
43推 17:15 "I do not ask Thee to take them out of the world, but to keep them from the evil [one.]
43推 17:16 "They are not of the world, even as I am not of the world.
43推 17:17 "Sanctify them in the truth; Thy word is truth.
43推 17:18 "As Thou didst send Me into the world, I also have sent them into the world.
43推 17:19 "And for their sakes I sanctify Myself, that they themselves also may be sanctified in truth.
43推 17:20 "I do not ask in behalf of these alone, but for those also who believe in Me through their word;
43推 17:21 that they may all be one; even as Thou, Father, [art] in Me, and I in Thee, that they also may be in Us; that the world may believe that Thou didst send Me.
43推 17:22 "And the glory which Thou hast given Me I have given to them; that they may be one, just as We are one;
43推 17:23 I in them, and Thou in Me, that they may be perfected in unity, that the world may know that Thou didst send Me, and didst love them, even as Thou didst love Me.
43推 17:24 "Father, I desire that they also, whom Thou hast given Me, be with Me where I am, in order that they may behold My glory, which Thou hast given Me; for Thou didst love Me before the foundation of the world.
43推 17:25 "O righteous Father, although the world has not known Thee, yet I have known Thee; and these have known that Thou didst send Me;
43推 17:26 and I have made Thy name known to them, and will make it known; that the love wherewith Thou didst love Me may be in them, and I in them. "
43推 18:1 When Jesus had spoken these words, He went forth with His disciples over the ravine of the Kidron, where there was a garden, into which He Himself entered, and His disciples.
43推 18:2 Now Judas also, who was betraying Him, knew the place; for Jesus had often met there with His disciples.
43推 18:3 Judas then, having received the [Roman] cohort, and officers from the chief priests and the Pharisees, *came there with lanterns and torches and weapons.
43推 18:4 Jesus therefore, knowing all the things that were coming upon Him, went forth, and *said to them, "Whom do you seek?"
43推 18:5 They answered Him, "Jesus the Nazarene." He *said to them, "I am [He.]" And Judas also who was betraying Him, was standing with them.
43推 18:6 When therefore He said to them, "I am [He]," they drew back, and fell to the ground.
43推 18:7 Again therefore He asked them, "Whom do you seek?" And they said, " Jesus the Nazarene. "
43推 18:8 Jesus answered, "I told you that I am [He]; if therefore you seek Me, let these go their way,"
43推 18:9 that the word might be fulfilled which He spoke, "Of those whom Thou hast given Me I lost not one."
43推 18:10 Simon Peter therefore having a sword, drew it, and struck the high priest's slave, and cut off his right ear; and the slave's name was Malchus.
43推 18:11 Jesus therefore said to Peter, "Put the sword into the sheath; the cup which the Father has given Me, shall I not drink it?"
43推 18:12 So the [Roman] cohort and the commander, and the officers of the Jews, arrested Jesus and bound Him,
43推 18:13 and led Him to Annas first; for he was father-in-law of Caiaphas, who was high priest that year.
43推 18:14 Now Caiaphas was the one who had advised the Jews that it was expedient for one man to die on behalf of the people.
43推 18:15 And Simon Peter was following Jesus, and [so was] another disciple. Now that disciple was known to the high priest, and entered with Jesus into the court of the high priest,
43推 18:16 but Peter was standing at the door outside. So the other disciple, who was known to the high priest, went out and spoke to the doorkeeper, and brought in Peter.
43推 18:17 The slave-girl therefore who kept the door *said to Peter, "You are not also [one] of this man's disciples, are you?" He *said, "I am not."
43推 18:18 Now the slaves and the officers were standing [there,] having made a charcoal fire, for it was cold and they were warming themselves; and Peter also was with them, standing and warming himself.
43推 18:19 The high priest therefore questioned Jesus about His disciples, and about His teaching.
43推 18:20 Jesus answered him, "I have spoken openly to the world; I always taught in synagogues, and in the temple, where all the Jews come together; and I spoke nothing in secret.
43推 18:21 "Why do you question Me? Question those who have heard what I spoke to them; behold, these know what I said."
43推 18:22 And when He had said this, one of the officers standing by gave Jesus a blow, saying, "Is that the way You answer the high priest?"
43推 18:23 Jesus answered him, "If I have spoken wrongly, bear witness of the wrong; but if rightly, why do you strike Me?"
43推 18:24 Annas therefore sent Him bound to Caiaphas the high priest.
43推 18:25 Now Simon Peter was standing and warming himself. They said therefore to him, "You are not also [one] of His disciples, are you?" He denied [it], and said, "I am not."
43推 18:26 One of the slaves of the high priest, being a relative of the one whose ear Peter cut off, *said, "Did I not see you in the garden with Him?"
43推 18:27 Peter therefore denied [it] again; and immediately a cock crowed.
43推 18:28 They *led Jesus therefore from Caiaphas into the Praetorium, and it was early; and they themselves did not enter into the Praetorium in order that they might not be defiled, but might eat the Passover.
43推 18:29 Pilate therefore went out to them, and *said, "What accusation do you bring against this Man?"
43推 18:30 They answered and said to him, "If this Man were not an evildoer, we would not have delivered Him up to you."
43推 18:31 Pilate therefore said to them, "Take Him yourselves, and judge Him according to your law." The Jews said to him, "We are not permitted to put anyone to death,"
43推 18:32 that the word of Jesus might be fulfilled, which He spoke, signifying by what kind of death He was about to die.
43推 18:33 Pilate therefore entered again into the Praetorium, and summoned Jesus, and said to Him, "Are You the King of the Jews?"
43推 18:34 Jesus answered, "Are you saying this on your own initiative, or did others tell you about Me?"
43推 18:35 Pilate answered, "I am not a Jew, am I? Your own nation and the chief priests delivered You up to me; what have You done?"
43推 18:36 Jesus answered, "My kingdom is not of this world. If My kingdom were of this world, then My servants would be fighting, that I might not be delivered up to the Jews; but as it is, My kingdom is not of this realm."
43推 18:37 Pilate therefore said to Him, "So You are a king?" Jesus answered, " You say [correctly] that I am a king. For this I have been born, and for this I have come into the world, to bear witness to the truth. Everyone who is of the truth hears My voice. "
43推 18:38 Pilate *said to Him, "What is truth?" And when he had said this, he went out again to the Jews, and *said to them, "I find no guilt in Him.
43推 18:39 "But you have a custom, that I should release someone for you at the Passover; do you wish then that I release for you the King of the Jews?"
43推 18:40 Therefore they cried out again, saying, "Not this Man, but Barabbas." Now Barabbas was a robber.
43推 19:1 Then Pilate therefore took Jesus, and scourged Him.
43推 19:2 And the soldiers wove a crown of thorns and put it on His head, and arrayed Him in a purple robe;
43推 19:3 and they [began] to come up to Him, and say, "Hail, King of the Jews!" and to give Him blows [in the face.]
43推 19:4 And Pilate came out again, and *said to them, "Behold, I am bringing Him out to you, that you may know that I find no guilt in Him."
43推 19:5 Jesus therefore came out, wearing the crown of thorns and the purple robe. And [Pilate] *said to them, "Behold, the Man!"
43推 19:6 When therefore the chief priests and the officers saw Him, they cried out, saying, "Crucify, crucify!" Pilate *said to them, "Take Him yourselves, and crucify Him, for I find no guilt in Him."
43推 19:7 The Jews answered him, "We have a law, and by that law He ought to die because He made Himself out [to be] the Son of God."
43推 19:8 When Pilate therefore heard this statement, he was the more afraid;
43推 19:9 and he entered into the Praetorium again, and *said to Jesus, "Where are You from?" But Jesus gave him no answer.
43推 19:10 Pilate therefore *said to Him, "You do not speak to me? Do You not know that I have authority to release You, and I have authority to crucify You?"
43推 19:11 Jesus answered, "You would have no authority over Me, unless it had been given you from above; for this reason he who delivered Me up to you has [the] greater sin."
43推 19:12 As a result of this Pilate made efforts to release Him, but the Jews cried out, saying, "If you release this Man, you are no friend of Caesar; everyone who makes himself out [to be] a king opposes Caesar."
43推 19:13 When Pilate therefore heard these words, he brought Jesus out, and sat down on the judgment seat at a place called The Pavement, but in Hebrew, Gabbatha.
43推 19:14 Now it was the day of preparation for the Passover; it was about the sixth hour. And he *said to the Jews, "Behold, your King!"
43推 19:15 They therefore cried out, "Away with [Him], away with [Him,] crucify Him!" Pilate *said to them, "Shall I crucify your King?" The chief priests answered, "We have no king but Caesar."
43推 19:16 So he then delivered Him to them to be crucified.
43推 19:17 They took Jesus therefore, and He went out, bearing His own cross, to the place called the Place of a Skull, which is called in Hebrew, Golgotha.
43推 19:18 There they crucified Him, and with Him two other men, one on either side, and Jesus in between.
43推 19:19 And Pilate wrote an inscription also, and put it on the cross. And it was written, "JESUS THE NAZARENE, THE KING OF THE JEWS."
43推 19:20 Therefore this inscription many of the Jews read, for the place where Jesus was crucified was near the city; and it was written in Hebrew, Latin, [and] in Greek.
43推 19:21 And so the chief priests of the Jews were saying to Pilate, "Do not write, 'The King of the Jews'; but that He said,' I am King of the Jews. '"
43推 19:22 Pilate answered, "What I have written I have written."
43推 19:23 The soldiers therefore, when they had crucified Jesus, took His outer garments and made four parts, a part to every soldier and [also] the tunic; now the tunic was seamless, woven in one piece.
43推 19:24 They said therefore to one another, "Let us not tear it, but cast lots for it, [to decide] whose it shall be"; that the Scripture might be fulfilled, "THEY DIVIDED MY OUTER GARMENTS AMONG THEM, AND FOR MY CLOTHING THEY CAST LOTS."
43推 19:25 Therefore the soldiers did these things. But there were standing by the cross of Jesus His mother, and His mother's sister, Mary the [wife] of Clopas, and Mary Magdalene.
43推 19:26 When Jesus therefore saw His mother, and the disciple whom He loved standing nearby, He *said to His mother, "Woman, behold, your son!"
43推 19:27 Then He *said to the disciple, "Behold, your mother!" And from that hour the disciple took her into his own [household.]
43推 19:28 After this, Jesus, knowing that all things had already been accomplished, in order that the Scripture might be fulfilled, *said, "I am thirsty."
43推 19:29 A jar full of sour wine was standing there; so they put a sponge full of the sour wine upon [a branch of] hyssop, and brought it up to His mouth.
43推 19:30 When Jesus therefore had received the sour wine, He said, "It is finished!" And He bowed His head, and gave up His spirit.
43推 19:31 The Jews therefore, because it was the day of preparation, so that the bodies should not remain on the cross on the Sabbath (for that Sabbath was a high [day]), asked Pilate that their legs might be broken, and [that] they might be taken away.
43推 19:32 The soldiers therefore came, and broke the legs of the first man, and of the other man who was crucified with Him;
43推 19:33 but coming to Jesus, when they saw that He was already dead, they did not break His legs;
43推 19:34 but one of the soldiers pierced His side with a spear, and immediately there came out blood and water.
43推 19:35 And he who has seen has borne witness, and his witness is true; and he knows that he is telling the truth, so that you also may believe.
43推 19:36 For these things came to pass, that the Scripture might be fulfilled, "NOT A BONE OF HIM SHALL BE BROKEN."
43推 19:37 And again another Scripture says, "THEY SHALL LOOK ON HIM WHOM THEY PIERCED."
43推 19:38 And after these things Joseph of Arimathea, being a disciple of Jesus, but a secret [one,] for fear of the Jews, asked Pilate that he might take away the body of Jesus; and Pilate granted permission. He came therefore, and took away His body.
43推 19:39 And Nicodemus came also, who had first come to Him by night; bringing a mixture of myrrh and aloes, about a hundred pounds [weight].
43推 19:40 And so they took the body of Jesus, and bound it in linen wrappings with the spices, as is the burial custom of the Jews.
43推 19:41 Now in the place where He was crucified there was a garden; and in the garden a new tomb, in which no one had yet been laid.
43推 19:42 Therefore on account of the Jewish day of preparation, because the tomb was nearby, they laid Jesus there.
43推 20:1 Now on the first [day] of the week Mary Magdalene *came early to the tomb, while it *was still dark, and *saw the stone [already] taken away from the tomb.
43推 20:2 And so she *ran and *came to Simon Peter, and to the other disciple whom Jesus loved, and *said to them, "They have taken away the Lord out of the tomb, and we do not know where they have laid Him."
43推 20:3 Peter therefore went forth, and the other disciple, and they were going to the tomb.
43推 20:4 And the two were running together; and the other disciple ran ahead faster than Peter, and came to the tomb first;
43推 20:5 and stooping and looking in, he *saw the linen wrappings lying [there;] but he did not go in.
43推 20:6 Simon Peter therefore also *came, following him, and entered the tomb; and he *beheld the linen wrappings lying [there,]
43推 20:7 and the face-cloth, which had been on His head, not lying with the linen wrappings, but rolled up in a place by itself.
43推 20:8 So the other disciple who had first come to the tomb entered then also, and he saw and believed.
43推 20:9 For as yet they did not understand the Scripture, that He must rise again from the dead.
43推 20:10 So the disciples went away again to their own homes.
43推 20:11 But Mary was standing outside the tomb weeping; and so, as she wept, she stooped and looked into the tomb;
43推 20:12 and she *beheld two angels in white sitting, one at the head, and one at the feet, where the body of Jesus had been lying.
43推 20:13 And they *said to her, "Woman, why are you weeping?" She *said to them, "Because they have taken away my Lord, and I do not know where they have laid Him."
43推 20:14 When she had said this, she turned around, and *beheld Jesus standing [there,] and did not know that it was Jesus.
